Huge, Foschini, Mr Price, Standard Bank: South Africa Stock Market Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-05-25T22:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/foschini-mr-price-standard-bank-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index rose 62.54, or 0.2
percent, to 31,793.59 at the 5 p.m. close of trading in
Johannesburg.  Huge Group Ltd. (HUG)  : The telecommunications company
said it has sold a 49 percent stake in TelePassport
Communications Ltd., a Namibian subsidiary, for 4.9 million rand
($696,992). Huge was unchanged at 1.25 rand.  MR Price Group Ltd. (MPC)  : The clothing retailer
publishes earnings results for the year ended April 2. MR Price
said on May 3 it expected per share earnings to rise by as much
as 53 percent in the 53 weeks to April 2. MR Price declined 67
cents, or 1.1 percent, to 63.26 rand.  Standard Bank  Group Ltd. (SBK SJ): Africa’s biggest bank
holds an annual shareholders’ meeting. The stock retreated 1
rand, or 1 percent, to 99.20 rand.  The  Foschini Group Ltd. (TFG)  : The clothing retailer
publishes results for the year ended in March. It said on April
18 that earnings will be up as much as 22 percent higher than a
year earlier. The shared declined 1.32 rand, or 1.5 percent, to
86.17 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
